				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Avatar of Dust<a name="58838"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 24 04 5:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>We just did this yesterday for the first time. We didn't really know what we were doing, but it worked out in the end. We had a team of kiters take the spiders (we spread out around the island while the last spider was being killed in the tunnel below (past the four way clearing). Chanters chain stuned the mobs that got past us. Not that many did, but the spiders stun and make short work anyone caught by them. The kiters run around the entire time, until Sig is dead. The reason you hold them the entire time is that they insta-respawn. So killing them is kind of pointless. We think there is a timer from when you kill the first trigger mob, but no one was sure what that was.
<br />

<br />
We didn't pull the Vorladian spawns away from the raid. Full raid and plenty of tanks, so we did multi-tank them when the Archwalkers died. Tanks were right there to take aggro, while casters were deeper in the tunnel. There were a lot of deaths. But other plans seem to include deaths as a matter of course, so hey. 
<br />

<br />
The Avatar himself is a pushover.</span></td>
