				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Avatar of Dust<a name="63139"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 20 04 12:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The simplest method is to have bards kite the adds.  Use DA song to get initial agro once they spawn.. and then you kite them the entire event.  
<br />

<br />
Monks will have to pull off the first big spider off of you but after that if you move your kite to near the rainbow then you will not get the other big spider agros except at the very end.
<br />

<br />
So start out kiting the whole circle, move the kite to the back after the first one is pulled off of you, then go to big circle when big big spider pops again.  You may wanna play DA song again at that point.
<br />

<br />
I have done this a few times and while it is a pain for the bard kiting the whole time (make sure to have back ups to pull the little spiders back up if they drift) it keeps the entire rest of your raid free to deal with the big guys.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
