			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Avatar of Dust<a name="67940"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 24 04 5:19 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I strongly suggest clearing most of the previous island as suggested.  Have a small team finish the last spider and then run to join your raid who is parked off to the side in either direction at the crossroads, to avoid aggoring the small spiders.  Have a kiter grab the mini-spiders (who rush to where the last mob died) and take them to the previous island for kiting.  Much less resources used than devoting a chanter team to them, and it gets the mini-spiders out of the way for the duration of the event - safer all around imo.
<br />

<br />
And definitely do the bard kite/highsun method for the 3 vorladian spawns, it works great.  I've been that bard for our successes and it really is not hard.  Have the small team finish off the archwalker and have your kiter-bard position between that team, and spider island.  When the 3 spiders pop and kill the small finish-off team, just tag them with bellow/hos or whatever and proceed to run em around spider island, and high-sun each of the first 2 as the raid is ready.  Then just run the third one down yourself to help with the kill.  Move raid back to where you want the Archwalker to die, rinse and repeat.
<br />

<br />
I'd really avoid any of the strats where you have people pulling mobs out of a kite, or having the mini spiders and larger spiders mixed in a kite.  It's just asking for trouble - the minis and larger spdiers run at different speeds which doesn't help.  And of course if you have a monk or whoever trying to pull mobs out of a pack of them, there's lots of bad things that can happen with aggro bouncing back and forth.  The above strat has nice clean aggro for both kiters (and ONLY those 2 kiters), and a nice empty spider island to work with short of event spawns and roamer repops.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
